    GimliVM - interactive talker environment

SYNOPSIS
    driver [options]

DESCRIPTION
    GimliVM opens up a predefined port allowing external connections
    to connect in its secure environment. Persons connected have a
    wide-varity of commands and options at their dispense, to better
    communicate with other connected persons. Options and so forth
    can be tuned in the configuration file, which is listed in the
    MANIFEST and documentation.

OPTIONS
    -v, --verbose
        Toggles the $verbose program flag, producing extra debugging
        output.

    -c, --config
        You may exlcusively specifiy your configuration file in the
        mannger of -c=<path> or --config=<path>

    -p, --port
        Setting this option with --port=<port number> will over-ride
        any pre-existing port varibles, including from the
        configuration file.

    -f, --fork
        Program will be forked off into the background.

    -q, --quit
        Program executes in quiet mode, nothing will be written to
        STDOUT

BUGS
    Millions upon millions, but none that I'm aware of. Please send
    bug reports to bugs@gimlivm.org

